Description:
Just gonna dump this here cause I was thinking about it.  If we launch it from the shell while in a specific Shopify theme directory, we could have a small Node server powering it and doing some processing.  It could be installed as a global npm package so that it can be run anywhere, and we could access the directory it was loaded from and offer the option to import the existing schemas from the theme for editing, something like:

```javascript
const themeSchema = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('src/sections/settings_schema.json', 'utf8'));
const sectionSchemas = globby
  .sync('src/sections/*.liquid')
  .map((sectionFile) => {
    const [, schema] = fs.readFileSync(sectionFile, 'utf8').match(/\{% ?schema ?%\}(.+?)\{% ?endschema ?%\}/);
    if (! schema) {
      return null;
    }
    return JSON.parse(schema);
  })
  .filter(schema => schema !== null);
```
